        "introduction": [
            {
                "titre": "There are many types of ways to protect yourself from rain—most often umbrellas and raincoats—but each comes with its own drawbacks. Umbrellas do a good job shielding your head and upper body, but your legs often get soaked, and worst of all, they occupy one of your hands. Raincoats tend to feel stuffy, and as they usually don't cover your face, you often end up getting cold and wet anyways.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "What if we could combine the two ideas, creating rain gear that provides great ventilation while not taking up your hands?",
                "sous_items": []
            }
        ],
